formThreeModelMf.noteCertificate:
1.	For verifying the cost and period of the project, we have relied on the work order issued by Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation to the concerned contractor for the purpose of construction of the multi-level parking and the period mentioned in the work order as well as approval of the competent authority for the extension of time limit of the project.

2.	For the purpose of verifying the number of units in the project, we have relied on the “Commencement letter” issued by Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation.


3.	The figures placed in the “customer receipts” and “others (if any)” in the sheet of “Means of Finance” have been put up on the basis of relevant documents like approval for floor rates by the department, approval of competent authority for booking the budget and other information provided for the means of finance by the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation vide it’s mail dated 27-11-2024.

4.	For the purpose of “incurred & paid expense” as mentioned in MOF of the project, we have considered the value of work completed as mentioned in the latest audited running account bill of the project

formThreeIdData.notesToCertificate:
1. The amount of construction cost has been considered on the basis of the information provided by the competent authorities of the Corporation.
2. The name of the RERA Bank account as per bank statement is "AMC RERA ACCOUNT FOR MULTILEVEL PARKING AN".
3. We have uploaded the minutes of meeting of Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority's (AUDA) "Land Disposal & Price Fixing Committee" held on 09-03-2023 as provided to us by the Estate Department of
Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation wherein the valued price of the plot of Prahladnagar Multilevel Parking (TP no.23+25 (Vejalpur) FP no.10+6 (Old FP no.117)) has been mentioned and approved and we have considered
the same for the registration purpose.
4. The carpet area of all the shops on all the floors of the multi-level parking has been considered based on the drawings of the project provided to us by the Road & Building Department whereas sale value of each floor has
been considered based on the floor rates of the project provided by the department vide it's letter no.5666 dated 30-11-2023 which has been proportionately distributed to each shop based on the carpet area as per department's drawings of the plan to derive the unit wise price for 98 shops.
5. This Form-3 for RERA registration is being filed as a response to the queries of RERA department.
